Could we consider camelCase instead of kebab-case for the metadata object keys?
I have the JS client in mind, where it would be more natural to operate on objects with the former.
const { columnNames, columnTypes } = queryMetadata;
// vs
const columnNames = queryMetadata["column-names"];
const columnTypes = queryMetadata["column-types"];

